Package com.redis.foundation.data

Class DataDoc

java.lang.Object
com.redis.foundation.data.DataDoc
public class DataDoc extends Object
A DataDoc manages a collection of data items representing a document.

    • addProperty

      public void addProperty(String aName, Object anObject)
      Add an application defined property to the data document.

      Notes:

      • The goal of the DataDoc is to strike a balance between providing enough properties to adequately model application related data without overloading it.
      • This method offers a mechanism to capture additional (application specific) properties that may be needed.
      • Properties added with this method are transient and will not be stored when saved or cloned.
      Parameters:
      aName - Property name (duplicates are not supported).
      anObject - Instance of an object.

    • isValid

      public boolean isValid()
      Convenience method examines all of the items in the document to determine if they are valid. A validation check ensures values are assigned when required and do not exceed range limits (if assigned).

      Note: If a item fails the validation check, then a property called Field.VALIDATION_PROPERTY_NAME will be assigned a relevant message.

      Returns:
      true or false

    • getValidationMessages

      public ArrayList<String> getValidationMessages()

      Returns:
      List of failed validation messages.

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      true or false
